ğŸ“Œ Overview
This program creates a unique dual-wave LED blinking pattern on the LPC2129 ARM7 microcontroller using 8 LEDs connected to Port 0 pins P0.16 to P0.23. 
The pattern includes center-outward blinking, outward-inward wave, alternating bit patterns, and full-blink effects.
It is an advanced pattern demonstrating bitwise operations, GPIO control, looping logic, and timing.

ğŸ”¹ Pattern Description

The program performs the following four sequences:

1ï¸âƒ£ Center â†’ Outward Wave

Starts from the middle two LEDs (P0.19 and P0.20)

Expands outward symmetrically

Creates a â€œpulse expandingâ€ visual effect

2ï¸âƒ£ Outward â†’ Center Wave

Reverse of the above

Creates a â€œpulse contractingâ€ effect

3ï¸âƒ£ Alternate LED Blinking

Displays: 10101010

Then: 01010101

Repeats for four cycles

Demonstrates binary masking and bit-shifting

4ï¸âƒ£ Full Blink Pattern

All LEDs ON

All LEDs OFF

Repeats 3 times

Simple but visually impactful

ğŸ”¹ Key Learning Points

Using bitwise shifts and masks to control LEDs

Implementing multi-phase LED wave animations

Writing readable and modular embedded C code

Controlling delay without timers (simple for beginners)

